images.description:
I don't do recipes.
Okay, I generally remember how I did it. Guestimate amounts.
Dough: 1 cup milk, 1 egg, 1/8 cup butter, 1 tsp salt, 1 tbsp yeast,. Soften yeast in water with 1 tsp sugar. Mix butter and liquids. Add 1 cup of flour. Mix well, add yeast. Add 1 cup flour, mix well. Scoop out half of the dough into another bowl. In one bowl, add 1 tbsp vanilla extract. In the other bowl, add 1/4 cup cocoa powder. Continue adding flour and mixing each until you have a soft dough. Cover and raise separately, 2 hours. Roll out each into squares. Spread butter on the chocolate layer. Place the vanilla layer on top. Fold in half. Cut in half the other way. Stack in alternating layers of color. Cut in half lengthwise vertically, through the center. Fold outward at the cut edges, put in greased pan. Cover and raise 1 hour. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes
